HEADWORD: Sacramentalist
<hw>Sac`ra*men"tal*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who holds the
doctrine of the real objective presence of Christ's body and blood in
the holy eucharist.</def> <rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

